	*** runtime/Jlib/foreign.java: fix bgl_string_hash that returned
	always 0!

	*** runtime/Jlib/foreign.java: fix bgl_setsockopt that called
	getsockopt instead of setsockopt!
	

Mon Apr 20 19:33:53 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** autoconf/thread: enable threads for Darwin.
	

Mon Apr 20 09:00:34 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* api/packrat: Add the packrat parser originally written in Scheme
	by Tony Garnock-Jones and adapted to Bigloo by Joseph Donaldson. (Thanks
	to you both.)
	

Mon Apr 20 07:13:58 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/sqlite/src/Llib/sqlite.scm: protect SQLite callbacks to let
	rollbacks execute after a user error.
	

Sun Apr 19 06:23:43 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail/src/Llib/vcard.scm: Fix vcard character set decoding.
	

Sun Apr 19 06:04:51 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Llib/thread.scm: export the nothread class to let clients
	such as Hop subclass it.
	

Sat Apr 18 19:37:19 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/os.scm: fix FILE-NAME-CANONICALIZE. Leading "../"
	sequences were incorrectly removed from the file name.
	

Sat Apr 11 07:11:03 CEST 2009 (Florian Loitsch):

	*** runtime/Clib/{cwriter,cports}.c: make stdout thread-safe by avoiding
	the data race between reading, writing, and flushing stdout.
	

Fri Apr 10 14:57:35 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Ast/unit.scm: fix DSSSL typed keyword arguments passing.
	

Fri Apr 10 06:55:49 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/[fp]thread: fix the library initialization for the JVM and
	DOTNET backend.
	

Thu Apr  9 19:59:24 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail/rfc2045.scm: fix a decoding error in quoted-printable
	(rfc2047 was incorrectly implicitly assumed).
	

Wed Apr  8 11:17:50 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** manual/core.texi: fix a typo in R5RS named let example.


Wed Apr  8 11:11:07 CEST 2009 (Florian Loitsch):

	* runtime: add close port hook to output procedure ports.
	

Thu Apr  2 07:26:41 CEST 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Ieee/input.scm: READ-OF-STRINGS now considers "xxx" tokens
	as strings independently of the characters inside the commas.

	* Complete brand new implementation for module name resolver. This
	gives greater flexibility and allow end-user to customize the 
	module name resolution. The first visible change is that now .afile are 
	per-directory.

	* A new user-parameter has been added to let end-users reacts to
	unknown module clauses inside eval.
	
	
Tue Mar 24 17:08:45 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Match/mexpand.scm: improve syntactic error messages.
	

Fri Mar  6 17:57:39 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/fthread/src/Posix/bglfthread.c: accustom initialization code
	for to thread-local-storage configuration.
	

Wed Mar  4 18:11:58 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Unsafe/hash.scm: add HASHTABLE-ADD! in replacement of
	HASHTABLE-UPDATE!

	*** runtime/Ieee/string.scm: fix string-capitalize that now consider
	that non ascii characters are letters. This ensure compatibility with
	UTF-8 encoding.
	

Tue Feb 24 13:03:34 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/api/text: add the text api (for now, only a bibtex parser).
	

Sun Feb 15 06:42:18 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/port.scm: add the new function CALL-WITH-INPUT-STRING.
	Fix CALL-WITH-xxx-FILE that were not correctly using UNWIND-PROTECT.
	

Tue Feb 10 14:26:15 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/capply.c: fix APPLY for functions of exactly 34 
	arguments. The 33th argument was incorrectly passed!
	

Sat Feb  7 07:13:15 CET 2009 (Cyprien Nicolas):

	*** {bdb,bdl}/Makefile, INSTALL: minor changes to allow users to compile
	Bee before installing Bigloo.
	

Fri Feb  6 07:53:52 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** jigloo/Makefile: fix the Makefile.
	

Thu Feb  5 17:55:40 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail/src/Llib/maildir.scm: minor fix in the folder validity
	checking machinery.
	

Mon Feb  2 10:48:58 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/csocket.c: fix GETADDRINFO usage.
	

Fri Jan 30 03:54:47 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail/src/Llib/maildir.scm: add customization for the maildir
	message base name (no longer required to be hostname).
	

Sun Jan 25 16:11:35 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/gstreamer/src/Llib/gstpadtemplate.scm: fix module initialization
	order.
	

Sun Jan 25 14:17:10 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/{Ast/build.scm,Module/class.scm}: fix -init-object-staged 
	that was incorrect when compiling modules not containing any class
	definition.
	

Sat Jan 24 02:46:13 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/evmodule.scm: yet another bug fix in the EVALuation
	of modules. Classes were created to soon, i.e., before the classes
	exported by the imported modules were actually bound in the module!
	

Wed Jan 21 18:41:43 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/expddefine.scm: fix a sever bug in the macro-expansion
	of eval DEFINE-METHOD. The body of the method was expanded with 
	the top-level expander instead of a define-aware local expander!


Tue Jan 20 18:31:40 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* api/mail/mailbox.scm: add the new function MAILBOX-FOLDER-MOVE!
	that moves an entire folder.
	

Tue Jan 20 14:35:52 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Clib/csocket.c: complete the switch to GETADDRINFO with
	the use of GETNAMEINFO for the inverse function. The socket 
	implementation is also updated with two improvements:
	  - inet_pton is used when inet_aton is not available (the previous
	    implementation based on inet_addr was just wrong).
	  - DNS lookup failures are now also cached.


Mon Jan 19 14:06:40 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Ast/unit.scm: fix the -safee compilation option. Types
	of dsssl #!key or #!optional arguments were not correctly enforced
	in the library (i.e., when compiled with "-unsafe -safee" flags).
	The was due to an erroneous evaluable? flag for the global representing
	the associated closure entry point.
	

Mon Jan 19 01:50:10 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Clib/csocket.c: use GETADDRINFO instead of GETHOSTBYNAME
	for architecture that supports it. GETADDRINFO is preferred because
	it is independent of IPv4/IPv6 and because it is re-entrant. Hence
	it is possible to avoid any lock for DNS queries.
	

Sat Jan 17 15:41:14 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/multimedia/src/mpd.scm: fix a type error in listalbum.
	

Wed Jan 14 17:04:01 CET 2009 (José Romildo)

	*** configure: fix MinGW Java configured class separartor.
	

Wed Jan 14 16:09:13 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** documentation/socket.texi: fix the socket documentation.


Wed Jan 14 16:09:02 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	********* Distribution of the release 3.2a.
        -------------------------------------------
	

Sun Jan  4 07:57:51 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/weakhash.scm: hashtable-update! for weak hash tables
	now returns the new updated object, as eager hash tables.
	

Sat Jan  3 20:01:59 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/multimedia/{musicproc,mplayer,mpg123}.scm: various fixes.


Thu Jan  1 06:06:53 CET 2009 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Llib/system.scm: add OS-CHARSET that returns the charset
	of the file system.
	

Wed Dec 31 14:14:17 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/unicode.scm: add extra characters encoding
	for utf8->iso-latin conversion.
	

Tue Dec 30 10:35:51 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Llib/os.scm: add GETUID, SETUID, GETPWNAM, and GETPWUID.
	

Tue Dec 23 21:08:26 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** configure: icc (Intel CC) fixes.
	

Fri Dec 19 08:17:26 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** gc: add Gentoo GC patches.

	*** gc: add a new bunch of patches and hacks for Sparc/Linux.
	

Fri Dec 19 07:44:02 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/cports.c: fix gc_sendfile that was prematurely
	raising errors which yield the descriptors opened by sendfile left
	opened on error.
		

Thu Dec 18 16:35:27 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Clib/inline-alloc.c, Clib/socket.c}: minor C
	fixes.
	

Thu Dec 18 11:43:30 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* manuals: add a (rough) documentation page for the mail library
	that is now an official component of the Bigloo environment.
	

Thu Dec 18 05:46:03 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Ieee/port.scm: fix MAKE-DIRECTORIES that was incorrect
	for path names ending with (FILE-SEPARATOR), e.g. "/tmp/foo/bar/".
	

Wed Dec 17 13:32:22 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime: various minor fixes for the Intel C compiler (icc).

	*** comptime/Coerce/app.scm: small improvement on the type checking
	of tail calls. The return type of local tails calls is no longer
	checked because this was introducing dead code that leaded to warnings
	with some C compilers (e.g., icc).
	

Wed Dec 17 11:06:57 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/expdrecord.scm: Modification of the expansion of
	records. Records no longer use the last field as a signature. They
	are now 100% compatible with structure. They differ from structure
	by their key that is forged from the name of the record. The key 
	associated with record types is the name of the record surrounded
	with '<' and '>' signs.

Wed Dec 17 09:02:48 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/unicode.scm: fix the UTF-8 decoding that was wrong
	for the #xc4...#xdf code points!
	

Mon Dec 15 09:36:42 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/vector.scm: add VECTOR-APPEND.

	*** runtime/Eval/evclass.scm: fix evaluated classes serialization.
	

Wed Dec 10 19:16:11 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime: pre-allocate bignum literals.
	

Wed Dec 10 16:47:09 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail/src/Llib/maildir.scm: fix a bug in maildir implementation.
	Current selection UIDs where not correctly updated.
	

Mon Dec  8 11:12:59 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/sqlite/src/Llib/engine.scm: fix sqltiny add column.
	

Fri Dec  5 12:21:39 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/ports.scm: add the new function RESET-OUTPUT-PORT
	(see the documentation).
	

Wed Dec  3 18:43:53 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/gstreamer/src/Llib/gstmm-music.scm: fix gstreamer music player
	that was not correctly restoring the audio volume from songs to songs.
	

Wed Dec  3 14:23:35 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime: replace signbit with BGL_SIGNBIT. The C function signbit
	is only defined for C99 compiler (which gcc on arm is not).
	

Mon Dec  1 18:49:59 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** Enable parallel make for the Bigloo's bootstrap.
	

Fri Nov 28 11:45:22 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Llib/unicode.scm: add WINDOWS-1252/UTF-8 conversions.
	

Fri Nov 21 09:38:51 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Unsafe/url.scm: fix a bug in URL parsing (those whose
	abspath is "*").
	

Wed Nov 19 10:31:54 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/pthread/src/Posix/bglpcondvar.c: fix a bug in the posix
	implementation of CONDITION-VARIALBE-WAIT! The Posix C implementation
	was not properly updating the Bigloo state of the mutex! The result
	of this error were mutexes actually unlocked but also unlockable!
	

Thu Nov  6 03:38:58 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Unsafe/bignumber.scm: fix the pure-scheme implementation 
	of seed-random!

	*** runtime/Eval/evmeaning.scm: fix an error in the interpretation
	of module forms. The expressions contained inside an module include
	file were not correctly macro-expanded.

	*** comptime/Object/wide-access.scm: fix a bug in wide classes and
	libraries. Wide classes accessors were not correctly rebuilt on
	library heap restore.
	

Mon Nov  3 20:01:03 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/cports.c: fix a bug in procedure output ports flush.
	

Sat Nov  1 08:54:10 CET 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/cports.c: stdout is now automatically flushed out
	when chars are read from stdin.
	

Wed Oct 22 19:17:54 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/date.scm: fix the rfc2822 <-> date conversions.
	

Wed Oct 15 12:32:58 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime/Reduce/sbeta.scm: add a simple optimization for 
	straightforward early beta reduction (e.g., (string-length "foo" -> 3).
	

Fri Oct 10 16:53:14 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/evobject.scm: Fix an error in the macro expansion
	of eval WITH-ACCESS forms.
	

Tue Oct  7 08:56:28 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Jlib/foreign.java,CSlib/foreign.cs,Clib/cstring.c}:
	fix string comparison functions implementation.
	

Tue Sep 30 10:02:25 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Llib/dsssl.scm,Eval/evcompile.scm}: minor change
	in the byte-code compilation of lambda form (i.e., only under the
	interpreter) that prevents a double macro-expansion that used to
	be required. The main effect of this improvement is to minimize
	the memory required by the macro-expander.
	

Mon Sep 22 11:00:15 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime: add new socket functions (e.g., SOCKET-OPTION and 
	SOCKET-OPTION-SET!).
	

Thu Sep 18 15:19:46 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime: Add -init-object-staged mode that improve the initialization
	of OO programs. Using this new staged initialization process (first
	classes, then generic functions, then methods, and then top-level forms)
	it is now possible to use cyclic imports for modules using 
	mutually recursive classes et generic functions.
	

Thu Sep 18 11:13:32 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/ports.scm: add the output-port-flush-hook functions.
	

Wed Sep 17 05:52:37 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* add a new compiler stage that counts actually used class definition.
	This is used to removed unused exception declarations from the 
	generated C code.
	

Tue Sep 16 16:55:49 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/csocket.c: fix a stupidity in socket tuning.
	

Mon Sep 15 18:05:50 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	********* Distribution of the release 3.1b.
        -------------------------------------------
	

Mon Sep 15 08:17:24 CEST 2008 (Florian Loitsch, Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Llib,Clib,Jlib}/date.{scm,c,java}: various date fixes.
	

Fri Sep 12 10:07:47 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Tvector/access.scm: fix a typing error that prevented
	the JVM backend to correctly execute optimized programs.
	

Fri Sep 12 08:03:16 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Ast/remove.scm: add a fix point iteration to the dead
	code removal pass. The lack of fix point iteration was producing
	incorrect AST that were still containing code for some dead functions.
	

Fri Sep 12 07:14:07 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/cports.c: fix output pipes.
	

Mon Sep  8 18:02:54 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Foreign/jtype.scm: fix a bug in JVM class and array
	declarations. The Bigloo types denoting Java classes and arrays were
	not correctly defined so the coercion pass generated bad code.
	

Mon Sep  8 12:12:57 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* api/web. The XML parser has been slightly improved. It no longer
	returns an opaque "instruction" entry containing a string denoting
	the XML header. Instead, it returns a "xml-decl" entry with a
	alist of attributes.
	

Mon Sep  8 12:06:12 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Expand/define.scm: fix a stupidity in the internal define
	parser.
	

Sun Sep  7 18:54:24 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* brand new implementation of the output ports. The new ports use
	POSIX functions instead of C-ISO functions. This permits many 
	optimization that yield to a significant speed improvement.
	

Wed Sep  3 11:58:03 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** significant improvements of output ports.
	

Sun Aug 31 16:10:06 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** cigloo: adapt the Cigloo parser to the new implementation of
	RGC contexts (that are no longer preserved across read/rp calls).
	

Wed Aug 27 17:00:57 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/port.scm: add SEND-FILE (see the documentation).
	

Tue Aug 26 10:06:32 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Llib/socket.scm: the MAKE-SERVER-SOCKET accepts a new
	keyword :backlog argument, that can be used, on the C back-end,
	to control the stack size of (posix) listen.


Tue Aug 26 10:05:13 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime: the entire port API has been updated to allow users
	to use their own buffers when creating ports. This impact file IOs,
	strings IOs, procedures IOs, sockets IOs, process IOs, etc.

Fri Aug 22 17:43:27 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Rgc: small modification in the expansion of regular-grammar
	to avoid allocating closure for representing grammars. The variable
	THE-RGC-CONTEXT is no longer defined outside the function implementing
	the grammar but as a formal parameter of this function.
	

Fri Aug 22 16:22:31 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime/Engine/compiler.scm: add -pmem compiler option for
	memory profiling (with bglmem).
	

Fri Aug 22 15:17:32 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Llib/hash.scm: add CREATE-HASHTABLE, equivalent to 
	MAKE-HASHTABLE but uses keywords.

	* runtime/Llib/hash.scm: add STRING-HASH.
	

Thu Aug 21 13:24:01 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Makefile: fix an erroneous profiling rule that prevented
	bee to be compiled.
	

Thu Aug 21 09:18:16 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Llib/socket.scm,Clib/csocket.c}: major performance
	improvements of sockets.
	

Tue Jul 22 08:20:38 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* api/web/src/Llib/date.scm: add W3C date format support.
	

Mon Jul 21 16:33:27 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime: significant performance improvement of closures
	allocation. A stupidity in a renaming of some primitive functions 
	of the library was preventing an important optimization of closures 
	allocations. This optimization allows null-environment closures
	to be statically allocated.
	

Fri Jul 18 04:04:18 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/multimedia/src/Llib/mpc.scm: fix MPC event loop error
	handling.

	*** runtime/Llib/date.scm: add CURRENT-MICROSECONDS.
	

Thu Jun 12 09:15:00 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail/src/Llib/maildir: fix UIDVALIDITY update.
	

Mon Jun  9 11:48:19 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Unsafe/aes.scm: add functions or encrypting/decrypting texts
	using the AES symmetric algorithm.
	
	*** manuals: re-organization of the Bigloo manual.

Thu Jun  5 10:57:52 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/srfi4.scm: fix a bug in bound checking error
	notification.
	

Wed Jun  4 07:17:12 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Expand/expdsrfi0.scm: The form COND-EXPAND now may check
	if a library exists (see the documentation).

	* web/src/Llib/url.scm: enlarge the charset used for URLs password.
	The characters "<", ">", and " " are now accepted.

	*** Fix bit-ursh for the JVM backend.

	* runtime/Unsafe/sha1: add SHA-1 hashing.
	

Mon Jun  2 07:39:57 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* manuals/mulitmedia.texi: add the documentation for the 
	multimedia library.
	

Thu May 29 15:59:47 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Clib/cbignum.c,Ieee/fixnum.scm,Unsafe/bignum.scm}: fix
	a bug in the bignum multiplication (multiply by 0 was segfaulting!)
	and change the prototype of randombx which now accepts a range as
	parameter.
	

Wed May 28 11:23:39 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	********* Distribution of the release 3.1a.
        -------------------------------------------
	
	
