	*** configure: replace the definition of shell_rm and shell_mv because
	"type -p" was causing problem on some platforms and/or some shells.
	
	*** runtime/Llib/thread.scm: fix the default implementation of
	THREAD-SLEEP! and fix the documentation.
	

Sat May  3 06:23:58 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* thread: the library function MUTEX-STATE is now common to all
	threads implementation.
	

Fri Apr 18 17:34:04 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/pthread/src/Posix/bglpmutex.c: fix a bug in mutex_lock
	that was responsible of (rare) dead locks. These lock happened when
	a Unix signal handler was raised during a GC allocation and when
	the signal handler was also GC allocating.
	

Fri Apr 11 08:15:19 CEST 2008 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/eval: inline FX operators.
	
	*** runtime/Ieee/equiv.scm: fix EQUAL for #e and #l exact numbers.

	
