	runs when using bigboot entry.
	

Sun Aug 19 07:19:54 CEST 2007 (Jose Romildo):

	*** runtime/comptime: Various integer arithmetic patches:

	I am working on some patches to add general integer procedures to Bigloo
        in the cases they are missing. By general integer procedure I mean a
        procedure that accepts any integer as arguments (fixnum, elong or llong)
        and dispatches to a more specific procedure doing type convertion when
        needed. Like the procedure + or * do for numbers.
        
        1) bigloo3.0b-integer.patch.bz2
        
           This patch changes the integer? procedure so that it also considers
           elong and llong numbers as integers.
        
           One question here: (integer? x) returns true, where x is a float
           number without a fractional part. This invalidates programs that test
           for integers using integer? prior to calling an integer specific
           procedure. For instance:
           
           (define (f x)
             (if (integer? x)
                 (quotient x 8)
        	 0))
        
           (f 20)   => 2
           (f 20.0) => type error: integer expected
        
           Other Scheme implementations (I have tried mzscheme) are able to
           compute (quotient 20.0 8), giving the answer 2.0, but fails to
           compute (quotient 20.1 8), giving an error type.
        
        2) bigloo3.0b-even.patch.bz2
        
           Currently there are three procedures that checks if an integer value
           is even:
        
           even? fixnum
           evenelong? elong
           evenllong? llong
        
           while there should be four:
        
           even? int
           evenfx? fixnum
           evenlong? elong
           evenllong? llong
        
           where the first one would check the type of its argument and call the
           apropiate one from the others.
        
           The same applies to the odd procedures.
        
           The patch also fixes the procedures evenelong?, evenllong?, oddelong?
           and oddllong?, which are currently wrong.
        
        3) bigloo3.0b-min.patch.bz2
        
           There are procedures minfx and maxfx, but minelong, maxelong,
           minllong, maxllong are missing. This patch adds them.
        
        4) bigloo3.0b-quotient.patch.bz2
        
           Currently quotient is implemented with three procedures:
        
           quotient fixnum fixnum
           quotientelong elong elong
           quotientllong llong llong
        
           In this case there should be four procedures:
        
           quotient int int
           quotientfx fixnum fixnum
           quotientelong elong elong
           quotientllong llong llong
        
           and the first one would check the type of its argument and call the
           others as appropriate, making convertions when needed. For instance,
        
           (quotient #l78654 3)
        
           would call
        
           (quotientllong #l78654 (fixnum->llong 3))
        
           The same is also valid for the remainder and modulo functions.
        
        The definitions are changed in file runtime/Ieee/fixnum.scm. Other
        Scheme source files are modified so that the fx version is called
        instead of the general one, reflecting these changes. For instance,
        quotientfx is called instead of quotient in the remaining source code.
        
        The patches are suposed to be applied in the order presented above.
        
        There is a problem with the last patch: compilation is aborted with an
        internal error message:
        
           *** INTERNAL-ERROR: Illegal signal caught
        
        that I cannot explain. So if you find the time to take a look at it, I
        will be grateful.
        
        The patches and some test programs are attached.
        
        There are other procedures like gcd that I have not yet handled, as I
        came across the INTERNAL-ERROR above.
        
	
Sun Aug 19 07:19:18 CEST 2007 (Tim Daly):

	*** configure: fix MacOS auto-configuation.
	

Sun Aug 19 07:18:45 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/cports.c: fix REOPEN-INPUT-PORT on string ports.
	

Wed Aug 15 07:57:42 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Ast/unit.scm: fix a bug in the typing of DSSSL keywords
	only functions.
	
	*** comptime/Module/impuse.scm: fix the error message displayed
	in case of inconsistent module initialization.

	*** comptime/Cgen/{cc,ld}.scm: source and destination file names
	may now contains space characters.
	
	
Tue Aug 14 11:49:38 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** Tools/shape.scm: transform the error message of global-shape
	into a simple warning. This is due to an inline bug the SHOULD BE
	fixed as soon as possible.

	The bug concerns library and inline functions calling inline functions
	(such as an inline function calling a class accessors).	The body of
	the inline function is inlined so it no longer refers to another 
	inline function. The original body of the accessors refers 
	to fully qualified inline function which, in case of a class
	accessor is static and rebinds with a different modules name in
	the module importing the library.

	In other words, this bugs prevent libraries from exporting inline
	functions that calls to class accessors.
	

Sun Aug 12 15:12:03 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/mail,runtime/Llib/date.scm: migrate rfc2822 date function
	to the standard library.
	

Sat Aug 11 06:00:56 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** recette/string.scm: fix an error UNSIGNED-STRING test.

	*** recette/extern-c.scm: manage to get rid of a warning message.


