Mon Jun 11 10:45:55 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** Fix the non custom GC configuration. It had been made erroneous
	by the introduction of the 7th brand of Boehm's collector.
	

Mon Jun 11 07:42:48 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** Re-design of the library init mechanism. Each library now comes
	with its own entry point. This makes the whole system more complex
	because the compiler and the loader now have to agree on conventions
	when loading dynamic libraries but this was needed because some systems 
	(guess which) emit a warning when two libraries export the same 
	symbol.
	

Sat Jun  9 09:32:16 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/base64.scm: fix a bug in the base64 string decoder.
	

