	*** runtime/llib/base64.scm: base64 encoding now accepts an optional
	padding argument that defaults to 64.
	

Wed May  9 16:39:37 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/base64.scm: significant performance improvement for
	base64 decoding.

	*** runtime/Llib/base64.scm: add PEM-READ-FILE and PEM-DECODE-PORT
	(see the documentation).
	

Thu May  3 14:52:25 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/base64.scm: fix base64 encoding/decoding (lines are
	now padded).

	* runtime/Llib/base64.scm: add BASE64-ENCODE-PORT and 
	BASE64-DECODE-PORT.
	

Tue Apr 24 05:28:38 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* bmacs/bee/bee-indent.el: improve the indenting of quoted lists
	and vectors.
	
	*** manuals/thread.texi: improve the documentation of multi-threading.

	
Mon Apr 23 14:54:50 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime: Add the -Wvariables to enable variable overriding
	error messages which are from now on, disabled by default.

	*** comptime: Fix the Java methods duplicate definitions warning
	messages.
	

Mon Apr 23 12:12:29 CEST 2007 (Stephane Epardaud):

	* api/ssl/ssl: Add server socket support, certificate, and private key
	support.
	

Mon Apr 23 07:17:24 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/R5Rs/hygien.scm: fix BIND-EXIT hygienic expansion.
	

Mon Apr 23 07:06:51 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Ieee/string.scm: in order to conform to SRFI-13, 
	STRING-INDEX and STRING-INDEX-RIGHT now return #f when the prefix
	is not found (they used to return -1).
	

Sat Apr 21 06:38:42 CEST 2007 (Dean Ferreyra):

	* bde/bdepend: add a command line option to select the suffix
	of object files.
	

Wed Apr 18 15:50:42 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** configure: change java version detection. As suggested by Y. Bres
	the new version uses javac instead of java.
	

Sat Apr 14 15:56:23 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/string.scm: add STRING-NATURAL-COMPARE and
	STRING-NATURAL-COMPARE-CI.
	

Wed Apr 11 11:53:26 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Match/descr.scm: Fix the pattern matching of structure
	that was just incorrect. It made Bigloo Solaris crash but it should
	have crashed on all platforms because it was just randomly accessing
	the memory.
	

Sat Mar 31 14:21:23 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/sqlite/engine.scm: SQLtiny tables constraints integrity  
	were not correctly dumped on the table!

	
Sat Mar 31 05:19:13 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime/initial.scm: optimize static pregex forms whose regexp
	is a constant string.
	

Sat Mar 31 05:12:13 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** doc: document XXXfl functions and byte-code-compile and byte-code
	run functions.
	

Sun Mar 25 14:47:09 CEST 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/multimedia/src/Llib/id3.scm: fix id3v2.2 parsing.
	

Sat Mar 24 08:27:10 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/output.scm: add WRITE-BYTE.
	

Wed Mar 21 15:03:18 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/cports.c: fix timeout I/O on MacOS X.
	

Fri Mar 16 05:53:47 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** api/web/src/Llib/xml.scm: improve the generic XML parser.
	

Tue Mar  6 09:25:37 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/expdrecord.scm: re-implementation of SRFI-9.
	

Fri Mar  2 15:41:30 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Include/bigloo.h: change the type of
	struct exitd -> exit to void * in order to avoid the cast in
	the JUMP_EXIT macro. This is needed because it looks like that on
	some systems (i.e., cygwin) sigsetjmp is compiled as macro that
	takes the address of its argument. Casting in JUMP_EXIT yields to
	&((void *)...) which is refused by GCC with that says something such
	as "illegal & in lvalue".
	

Mon Feb 26 07:26:19 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/vector.scm: Add SRFI-43 vector-copy!.
	

Thu Feb 22 15:03:51 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/csocket.c: yet another DNS cache bug fix.
	

Sun Feb 18 09:59:40 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** I have backported the GC blocking machinery (that used to
	be working with GC_start_blocking/GC_end_blocking and that is now
	working with GC_do_blocking). Lacking this support with the Boehm's
	GC version 7 was causing spurious errors during sendfile.
	

Tue Feb 13 13:47:19 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/port.scm: add output procedure ports.
	

Sat Feb 10 09:38:52 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/string.scm: add STRING-INDEX-RIGHT and fix
	STRING-INDEX.
	

Fri Feb  9 09:20:09 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** Switch to Boehm's GC version 7.
	

Tue Feb  6 13:33:17 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Jlib/socket.java: JVM sockets now use buffered IOs.
	

Tue Feb  6 13:04:05 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* The WITH-HANDLER form now also intercepts Java exceptions.
	

Thu Feb  1 06:37:46 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/binary.scm: FLUSH-BINARY-PORT added.

	*** runtime/Ieee/vector.scm: SORT now accepts the procedure
	as first argument. It maintains backward compatibility with second
	argument procedure but this convention is now deprecated.

	*** configure: In addition to stdlibint the configuration process
	also checks unistdint (mainly for Solaris).

	*** api/web/src/Llib/url.scm: fix relative (e.g., file) urls parsing.
	

Mon Jan 22 15:43:44 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Unsafe/intext.scm: fix custom class 
	serialization/deserialization. The Java implementation was incorrect
	because of a bad call to assq instead of assv.
	

Thu Jan 11 07:26:48 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime: Fix the evaluation environment of DSSSL default values.
	They are now evaluated in a environment where the fixed parameters
	are bound.
	

Wed Jan 10 19:52:38 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/evmodule.scm: Fix load eval module implementation.

	
Mon Jan  8 11:40:31 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime: add -static-all-library flags.
	

Sat Jan  6 09:18:37 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	* comptime/runtime: static class can now be declared inside module
	body (this is unfortunately imposed by Snow).
	

Wed Jan  3 13:42:50 CET 2007 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Llib/socket.scm: fix the socket exit register function
	that was loosing the exit value.
	

