	*** bmacs: minor Xemacs portability fixes.
	

Fri Nov 17 14:24:16 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Unsafe/gunzip.scm: fix an unzip stupidity.
	

Thu Nov 16 17:25:12 CET 2006 (Dominique Boucher):

	*** runtime/Lalr/lalr.scm: Fix the none: associativity problem.
	

Wed Nov 15 12:09:56 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/macros.scm: Prepare for module macros.
	They will be defined locally in the current module. That is a macro 
	defined inside a module will no longer be visible from the other 
	modules.
	

Mon Nov 13 21:35:45 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/capply.c: fix stupid apply bug that occurred for
	function with more than 32 arguments. The stack frame holding 
	actual values was always 32 cells large!
	

Sun Nov 12 19:20:59 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Ieee/fixnum.scm: fix the prototype of =elong and =llong
	that were incorrectly declared as ::belong and ::bllong instead
	of ::elong and ::llong.
	

Sun Nov 12 19:13:57 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Unsafe/md5.scm: improve the performance of MD5 digest.
	Change the prototype of MD5SUM. Add MD5SUM-MMAP, MD5SUM-STRING,
	MD5SUM-PORT, and MD5SUM-file.
	

Fri Nov 10 15:00:24 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Expand/eps.scm: macro-expansion is not split in two
	stage. One for user macros, one for compiler optimization and
	debug. This is needed for detecting library function overriding 
	before optimization.


Fri Nov 10 11:44:28 CET 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Clib/csocket.c: fix HOST and HOSTINFO C implementation.
	
	*** comptime/Expand/{lambda,object}.scm: Fix macro expansion for
	inner defines.
	
	
