	*** runtime/Eval/evmeaning.scm: fix a nasty problem that prevented
	correct error messages for optimized interpreted operators (e.g., 
	CADR).
	

Sat Oct 14 08:45:39 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	* runtime/Ieee/string.scm: implement SRFI-13 STRING-PREFIX-XXX
	and STRING-SUFFIX-XXX functions.
	

Wed Oct 11 09:00:15 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/expand.scm: fix a sever bug in the macro expansion
	mechanism. Defining a macro was not thread-safe! The macro table
	was lacking a lock mechanism!
	

Mon Oct  9 13:41:26 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{J,CS}lib/input_pipe_port.{java,cs}: fix open_input_pipe
	in Java and Dotnet.
	

Sat Oct  7 11:58:47 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/{evmodule,evcompile}.scm: fix eval module include
	form (which was totally broken).
	

Sat Oct  7 11:11:23 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/evobject.scm: fix the eval macro expansion of 
	INSTANTIATE:: in presence of virtual slots.
	

Tue Oct  3 11:55:50 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** comptime/Globalize/integration.scm: big changes in the 
	integration technique. The new one is much more efficient for
	codes containing a lot of local functions. Since is a brand
	new algorithm highly critical (in term of performance and correctness)
	I have left the old algorithm accessible (see the
	-fold-closure-integration option). This change in the compiler
	will justify the entering of the 2.9 series.
	

Mon Oct  2 17:49:29 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Unsafe: the library modules that are know to be safe are
	now compiled in unsafe mode (this applies to kmp, tar, and gunzip).
	

Mon Oct  2 09:33:47 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/{Eval/expddefine.scm,Clib/c{control,apply}.c}: fix 
	variable arity eval generic functions and methods (i.e, 
	DEFINE-GENERIC and DEFINE-METHOD within the interpreter).
	

Mon Oct  2 07:55:26 CEST 2006 (Manuel Serrano):

	*** runtime/Eval/evmeaning.scm: fix error message for unbound variable.
	The report culprit module is the module where the variable reference
	occurred. It is no longer the current module evaluating the expression.
	

